The paper deals with the problem of neural ranking for information retrieval, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques (cs.CL) and machine learning algorithms (cs.LG, cs.AI) for improving the performance of neural ranking models. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image captioning datasets (cs.CV) for weak supervision, indicating a potential connection to computer vision.
